" <div class=\"graphic\">",
"  <div class=\"figure\" style=\"width: 524px\">",
"   <div class=\"ttl\">",
"    Ultrasound of gouty arthritis of the metacarpophalangeal joint",
"   </div>",
"   <div class=\"cntnt\" style=\"width: 504px; height: 200px; background-image: url(data:image/jpeg;base64,);\">",
"   </div>",
"   <div class=\"lgnd\">",
"    This longitudinal dorsal ultrasound scan of the second metacarpophalangeal joint shows thickened synovium with hyperechoic deposits (white arrow) indicative of crystalline arthropathy. The double contour sign at the metacarpal head (yellow arrow) represents crystal deposition on the articular cartilage surface. The findings in this 56-year-old man with polyarthritis are consistent with gout.",
